## File formats: what we actually know

### `L*.MAP` — **strong**

| Fact | Confidence |
|------|------------|
| Raw binary, no compression on load | Confirmed (FCB dumps = on-disk bytes) |
| LA = 3840 B ≈ **38×100** cells, stride **100** on X | Confirmed in ICON1 (`×0x64`) |
| Cell = **1 byte stamp id** (full value, not only lo7) | Confirmed (draw uses full AL) |
| Id → stamp at `DS:207A + id×24` | Confirmed |
| Stamp = **2×6 text cells**, on-disk bank **`attr,char`** | Strong (draw loop + BA stats) |
| Bank size: BA = 96 stamps; **BA‖BB ≈ 192** covers ids up to ~180 | Strong hypothesis |
| Bit 7 often set on “solid-ish” cells | Observed; exact flag meaning partial |
| Camera / scroll / exact match to one B800 frame | **Not locked** (~45% direct / high only with overfit maps) |

So: we know **how the file is shaped and how the engine consumes it**, not a complete “authoring format + all edge rules” doc.

### `L*.ADV` — **partial**

ASCII CR/LF, optional `1Ah` padding. Skeleton for LA:

| Line | Example | Status |
|------|---------|--------|
| `3 3` | spawn? | *hypothesis* |
| `2 2` | secondary / camera? | *hypothesis* |
| **`2880 2400`** | world origin | **Confirmed** (ICON1 subtracts then `/288`) |
| `14 20` | room grid / logical size? | *hypothesis* |
| `250`, `8`, warp table, `86 67` | timers / links / junk | *hypothesis* |

We have **not** walked every ADV field to the instruction that reads it.

### `*.DAT` — **several different formats**

| File | Role | Format understanding |
|------|------|----------------------|
| **`BA.DAT` / `BB.DAT`** | Terrain stamp banks | **Strong** (2304 B, 24 B = 2×6 cells, attr/char) |
| **`L*.DAT`** | Level object / placement (ASCII family) | **Weak** — structure not fully mapped |
| **`M*.DAT` / `M*.ADV`** | Monsters | **Partial** — ASCII names + numbers (HP, scores) |
| **`DR.DAT` / `SP.DAT`** | Sprites / labels | **Partial** — length-prefixed names + binary frames |
| **`ICON#.GAM`** | Saves | Named only (FCBs); not reverse-engineered |

So: **not** “we know all ADV/MAP/DAT formats.” We know **MAP + terrain banks** best; ADV/level DAT/monsters/sprites are notes, not finished specs.

